I need to take this call.

00:15:36.380 --> 00:15:41.340
Maryland is going to play out
in a way that will, hopefully,

00:15:41.418 --> 00:15:42.977
correct the wrongs
of California,

00:15:43.053 --> 00:15:46.352
but that's yet to be seen.

00:15:46.423 --> 00:15:49.222
The reality is
that the far right,

00:15:49.292 --> 00:15:51.284
as well as the
African American leadership

00:15:51.361 --> 00:15:52.795
that they've been able
to amass,

00:15:52.863 --> 00:15:54.296
is going to do
what they do.

00:15:54.364 --> 00:15:56.128
They've been doing it
all over the country.

00:15:56.199 --> 00:15:58.190
And they go in the pulpit
and they use the pulpit

00:15:58.268 --> 00:15:59.827
as a space of hate

00:15:59.903 --> 00:16:01.962
to undermine

00:16:02.039 --> 00:16:03.370
people's rights.

00:16:03.440 --> 00:16:06.432
—The strategy of the right

00:16:06.510 --> 00:16:10.344
has always been
a strategy of fear.

00:16:10.414 --> 00:16:14.282
Not only produce fear,
but to use it skillfully

00:16:14.351 --> 00:16:17.286
to get people of color
to cross over

00:16:17.354 --> 00:16:20.449
and become a part
of the radical right.

00:16:20.524 --> 00:16:25.826
It has happened to us over
and over and over again.

00:16:25.896 --> 00:16:29.195
Cincinnati City Council
voted 7-2

00:16:29.266 --> 00:16:31.792
to pass what was called
the Human Rights Ordinance.

00:16:31.868 --> 00:16:35.202
The purpose of this ordinance
was to elevate

00:16:35.272 --> 00:16:38.105
one’s sexual preference
to protected—class status.

00:16:38.175 --> 00:16:41.372
But many local citizens
were outraged,

00:16:41.445 --> 00:16:46.212
including...

00:16:46.283 --> 00:16:47.716
The Human Rights Ordinance
that was passed

00:16:47.784 --> 00:16:50.048
in November of 1992

00:16:50.120 --> 00:16:52.555
basically said that
you cannot discriminate

00:16:52.622 --> 00:16:56.354
based on housing or jobs.

00:16:56.426 --> 00:17:00.920
It just mirrored what
the 1964 Civil Rights Act did.

00:17:00.997 --> 00:17:03.489
We drafted legislation

00:17:03.567 --> 00:17:05.660
that would change
the city charter,

00:17:05.735 --> 00:17:07.101
that said you cannot
pass any laws

00:17:07.170 --> 00:17:09.605
based on
sexual orientation.

00:17:09.673 --> 00:17:11.732
We had to collect signatures
to put it on the ballot,

00:17:11.808 --> 00:17:14.209
so, obviously, those were
circulated in the churches

00:17:14.277 --> 00:17:16.576
and it was amazing,

00:17:16.646 --> 00:17:19.411
the support we got from the
African American community,

00:17:19.483 --> 00:17:21.883
even Fred Shuttlesworth.

00:17:21.952 --> 00:17:23.818
He was considered one
of the big three

00:17:23.887 --> 00:17:26.413
and he lived herein Cincinnati
and he wanted to help us.

00:17:32.429 --> 00:17:34.022
I know quite a few things

00:17:34.097 --> 00:17:35.895
about fighting
discrimination.

00:17:35.966 --> 00:17:40.767
Cincinnati Issue 3
is not about discrimination.

00:17:40.837 --> 00:17:44.205
This was probably
the highwater mark

00:17:44.274 --> 00:17:46.834
for the African American
community

00:17:46.910 --> 00:17:49.436
and the evangelical
white community,

00:17:49.513 --> 00:17:51.071
to work together
on an issue.

00:17:51.148 --> 00:17:53.548
The biggest tool
we had was

00:17:53.617 --> 00:17:56.279
KZ Smith.

00:17:56.353 --> 00:17:58.753
—Last November,
the voters came out

00:17:58.822 --> 00:18:02.156
and 62% asked to repeal
our Human Rights Ordinance.

00:18:02.225 --> 00:18:03.625
—And that 62%

00:18:03.693 --> 00:18:06.629
against an ordinance
which would have specifically

00:18:06.696 --> 00:18:08.096
protected homosexuals —-

00:18:08.165 --> 00:18:09.723
—Understand —-

00:18:09.799 --> 00:18:11.165
Was voted significantly so

00:18:11.234 --> 00:18:12.964
by the black community,
is that not so’?

00:18:13.036 --> 00:18:14.731
What black people need
to understand is that

00:18:14.804 --> 00:18:17.899
gays are trying to become
the new minority.

00:18:17.974 --> 00:18:21.137
And, if blacks don't wake up,
they'll be back

00:18:21.211 --> 00:18:23.942
on the back
of the bus again.

00:18:24.014 --> 00:18:26.346
It was, to me, in my mind,
trying to legitimize

00:18:26.416 --> 00:18:27.850
the gay lifestyle.

00:18:27.918 --> 00:18:30.182
I was the president of the
Baptist Ministers‘ Conference,

00:18:30.253 --> 00:18:32.085
at the time.

00:18:32.155 --> 00:18:34.089
A group of people had come
to me, asking if I would be

00:18:34.157 --> 00:18:36.023
the spokesperson for it.

00:18:36.092 --> 00:18:39.153
What troubles me is
that people can't believe

00:18:39.229 --> 00:18:41.220
that we actually stood up
for what we believed.

00:18:41.298 --> 00:18:43.391
They think that
we were motivated

00:18:43.466 --> 00:18:45.765
by the religious right,
that we were motivated

00:18:45.835 --> 00:18:48.964
by rich white people coming
into the community

00:18:49.039 --> 00:18:51.838
and telling us what to believe
and what to stand up for,

00:18:51.908 --> 00:18:53.968
versus us thinking
for ourselves

00:18:54.044 --> 00:18:55.671
and believing for ourselves.

00:18:55.745 --> 00:18:59.147
I believed that
homosexuality was wrong

00:18:59.216 --> 00:19:02.947
before I met a Phil Burress
or anybody else.

00:19:03.019 --> 00:19:05.283
We knew that, if we
could get the message out

00:19:05.355 --> 00:19:08.689
that the African Americans
were offended by this —-

00:19:08.758 --> 00:19:09.851
not me,

00:19:09.926 --> 00:19:11.360
not the white folk.

00:19:11.428 --> 00:19:13.453
It was too easy
to pigeonhole us

00:19:13.530 --> 00:19:15.862
and saying
we're just hatemongers,

00:19:15.932 --> 00:19:20.199
but when an African American got
up and delivered the message,

00:19:20.270 --> 00:19:21.897
they didn't touch them.

00:19:21.972 --> 00:19:24.167
They didn't say a word about
them. They were afraid of them.

00:19:24.241 --> 00:19:26.232
That's the reason why
we got sexual immorality.

00:19:26.309 --> 00:19:28.573
That's the reason why there's
a rise in the gay agenda.

00:19:28.645 --> 00:19:32.479
—You can be converted!
You were not born that way!

00:19:32.549 --> 00:19:34.540
The black church,
to this day,

00:19:34.618 --> 00:19:37.985
remains fundamentally
conservative.

00:19:38.054 --> 00:19:39.488
You know, we preached
against smoking

00:19:39.556 --> 00:19:41.854
and drinking and drugging,
and even movies.

00:19:41.925 --> 00:19:46.226
The gay thing is something
the black church has not quite

00:19:46.296 --> 00:19:48.628
been able to grapple with.

00:19:48.698 --> 00:19:51.099
We think it's
a white man's disease

00:19:51.167 --> 00:19:52.533
and it was contagious

00:19:52.602 --> 00:19:54.195
[chuckling] and it got
on us, you know’?

00:19:54.271 --> 00:19:55.636
Well, I was already
a part of

00:19:55.705 --> 00:19:57.833
the evangelical fundamentalist
Pentecostal movement

00:19:57.907 --> 00:19:59.671
for generations.

00:19:59.743 --> 00:20:03.145
I stayed in those trenches,
almost until I was 50 years old.

00:20:03.213 --> 00:20:06.706
I'm in a miracle mood.
I'm in a healing mood.

00:20:06.783 --> 00:20:10.947
I knew that white people

00:20:11.021 --> 00:20:14.218
were using their influence
to buy my influence

00:20:14.291 --> 00:20:17.385
with the black church

00:20:17.460 --> 00:20:19.588
to advance their
antigay agenda

00:20:19.663 --> 00:20:21.255
and we bought into it.

00:20:21.331 --> 00:20:23.732
—Our nation is grateful.

00:20:23.800 --> 00:20:26.735
There are a few
prominent leaders

00:20:26.803 --> 00:20:28.396
who have a voice
in the media,

00:20:28.471 --> 00:20:31.600
who have been
influenced and embraced

00:20:31.675 --> 00:20:34.735
by nonblack
fundamentalist entities,

00:20:34.811 --> 00:20:37.974
funded, encouraged,

00:20:38.048 --> 00:20:39.709
given positions of
leadership and prominence

00:20:39.783 --> 00:20:41.273
in the political
and religious circles,

00:20:41.351 --> 00:20:44.116
and they're made
into voices of influence.

00:20:45.855 --> 00:20:48.085
—We may face an America,
in 10 years,

00:20:48.158 --> 00:20:50.092
where the problems that are
in the black community

00:20:50.160 --> 00:20:52.492
are in every community
in the land.

00:20:52.562 --> 00:20:55.623
We don't want an America
like that.

00:20:57.033 --> 00:21:00.333
WOMAN: Yeahl Whool

