00:22:09.773 --> 00:22:11.639
The black community is

00:22:11.708 --> 00:22:13.870
the southern central region,
which is all,

00:22:13.943 --> 00:22:18.540
you know,
Baltimore City on down.

00:22:18.615 --> 00:22:20.913
Wife and kids are absolutely
supportive of all of this.

00:22:20.984 --> 00:22:23.419
I mean, they believe in it.
They understand it.

00:22:23.486 --> 00:22:25.352
We have a lot of dialogue.
We've had questions.

00:22:25.422 --> 00:22:27.117
I mean, they asked me,
said "Well, Daddy,

00:22:27.190 --> 00:22:28.954
why don't you just let it go?"
Or, you know,

00:22:29.025 --> 00:22:30.891
"People should live the way
they should, right?"

00:22:30.960 --> 00:22:32.326
I said "Well,
think about it."

00:22:32.395 --> 00:22:33.886
So I try and challenge
them to think.

00:22:33.963 --> 00:22:36.364
You know, if you're
going to be the person

00:22:36.433 --> 00:22:39.664
that gets a news clip and thinks
2 to 3 minutes about this

00:22:39.736 --> 00:22:43.070
and says "Oh, equality sounds
fair. I guess I'll do it,"

00:22:43.139 --> 00:22:45.574
great, your mind's
going to be changed.

00:22:45.642 --> 00:22:48.441
But if you think past
that 5 or 10 minutes

00:22:48.511 --> 00:22:51.037
and start looking
at society at large

00:22:51.114 --> 00:22:53.173
and look at many
other factors,

00:22:53.249 --> 00:22:55.582
