a lot of outreach

00:24:17.433 --> 00:24:18.867
within the
black community.

00:24:18.935 --> 00:24:22.599
—One of the questions
in 2004, when Georgia

00:24:22.672 --> 00:24:24.106
was trying to pass
this amendment

00:24:24.173 --> 00:24:29.612
and we completely got lost and
it was embarrassing, really —-

00:24:29.679 --> 00:24:32.341
I did hear from a lot
of black gay people

00:24:32.415 --> 00:24:35.942
who felt that marriage was not
their number—one priority

00:24:36.019 --> 00:24:38.749
and it kind of stopped me,
like, you know,

00:24:38.821 --> 00:24:41.450
